title: Rick Springfield *LIVE* - At the Coronado Theater
description:
'80s Heartthrob, and former soap opera actor, Rick Springfield brings his band and their style of music to the Rockford, IL. area for a concert that was sure to attract most of the women in the area! Making the leap from soap actor to MTV "BeefCake" was easy for Rick with his string of hits in the '80s which included "Don't Talk to Strangers", "Jesse's Girl", "Will I Ever See You Again", "Affair of the Heart", "I've Done Everything for You", "You Better Love Somebody", and more. He also does a cover of Mister Mister's "These Broken Wings" and Gerry Rafferty's "Baker Street". 

This 1 hour and 20min (approx) concert was capped for your viewing pleasure courtesy of HDNet and upped per request by a "lady" friend of ours. Not that we had anything against Rick Springfield, it's just not our kind of music.....
